#, no-wrap
msgid "Hardware Requirements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Not all problems can be solved with better hardware, but choosing the right "
"hardware is an absolute necessity for large scale deployments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:3
msgid "The minimum requirements for the {productname} Server are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:4
msgid "EightÂ or more recent {x86_64} CPU cores."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:5
msgid "32{nbsp}GiB RAM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:6
msgid "For installations with thousands of clients, use 64{nbsp}GB or more."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:7
msgid "Fast I/O storage devices, such as locally attached SSDs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:8
msgid ""
"For PostgreSQL data directories, we recommend locally attached RAID-0 SSDs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:9
msgid ""
"If the {productname} Server is virtualized, enable the `elevator=none` "
"kernel command line option, for the best input/output performance.  You can "
"check the current status with [command]``cat /sys/block/<DEVICE>/queue/"
"scheduler``.  This command will display a list of available schedulers with "
"the currently active one in brackets.  To change the scheduler before a "
"reboot, use [command]``echo none > /sys/block/<DEVICE>/queue/scheduler``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:10
msgid "The minimum requirements for the {productname} Proxy are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:11
msgid ""
"One {productname} Proxy per 500-1000 clients, depending on available network "
"bandwidth."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:12
msgid "Two or moreÂ recent {x86_64} CPU cores."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:13
msgid "16{nbsp}GB RAM, and sufficient storage for caching."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Clients should never be directly attached to the {productname} Server in "
"production systems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:15
msgid ""
"In large scale installations, the {productname} Proxy is used primarily as a "
"local cache for content between the server and clients.  Using proxies in "
"this way can substantially reduce download time for clients, and decrease "
"Server egress bandwidth use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:16
msgid ""
"The number of clients per proxy will affect the download time.  Always take "
"network structure and available bandwidth into account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:17
msgid ""
"We recommend you estimate the download time of typical usage to determine "
"how many clients to connnect to each proxy.  To do this, you will need to "
"estimate the number of package upgrades required in every patch cycle.  You "
"can use this formula to calculate the download time:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "Size of updates * Number of clients / Theoretical download speed / 60\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:19
msgid ""
"For example, the total time needed to transfer 400{nbsp}MB of upgrades "
"through a physical link speed of 1{nbsp}GB/s to 3000 clients:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hardware-reqs.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "400 MB  * 3000 / 119 MB/s / 60 = 169 min\n"
msgstr ""

