#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:25
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:50
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"HUB_XMLRPC_API_URL = \"<HUB_XMLRPC_API_URL>\"\n"
"HUB_USERNAME = \"<USERNAME>\"\n"
"HUB_PASSWORD = \"<PASSWORD>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:26
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:51
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "client = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(HUB_XMLRPC_API_URL, verbose=0)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "hubSessionKey = client.hub.login(HUB_USERNAME, HUB_PASSWORD)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:28
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:53
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:73
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Get the server IDs\n"
"serverIds = client.hub.listServerIds(hubSessionKey)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# For simplicity, this example assumes you are using the same username and password here, as on the hub server.\n"
"# However, in most cases, every server has its own individual credentials.\n"
"usernames = [HUB_USERNAME for s in serverIds]\n"
"passwords = [HUB_PASSWORD for s in serverIds]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Each server uses the credentials set above, client.hub.attachToServers needs\n"
"# them passed as lists with as many elements as there are servers.\n"
"client.hub.attachToServers(hubSessionKey, serverIds, usernames, passwords)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Perform the operation\n"
"systemsPerServer = client.multicast.system.list_systems(hubSessionKey, serverIds)\n"
"successfulResponses = systemsPerServer[\"Successful\"][\"Responses\"]\n"
"failedResponses = systemsPerServer[\"Failed\"][\"Responses\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:32
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:56
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:75
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"for system in successfulResponses:\n"
"  print(system)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:33
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:57
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Log out\n"
"client.hub.logout(hubSessionKey)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example: Relay Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:35
msgid ""
"In relay authentication mode, the credentials used to sign in to the Hub API "
"are also used to sign in into the APIs of the peripheral servers the user "
"wants to work with.  In this authentication mode, it is assumed that the "
"same credentials are valid for every server, and that they correspond to a "
"user with appropriate permissions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:36
msgid ""
"After signing in, you must call the ``attachToServers`` method.  This method "
"defines the servers to target in all subsequent calls."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:37
msgid "A typical workflow for relay authentication is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Credentials for the Hub are passed to the ``loginWithAuthRelayMode`` method, "
"and a session key for the Hub is returned (``hubSessionKey``)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Using the session key from the previous step, {productname} Server IDs are "
"obtained for all the peripheral servers attached to the Hub via the ``hub."
"listServerIds`` method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:40
msgid ""
"A call to `attachToServers` is made, and the same credentials used to sign "
"in to the Hub are passed to each server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:43
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:63
msgid ""
"This is defined by ``serverIds``, which contains the IDs of the servers to "
"target.  In the background, ``system.list_system`` is called on each "
"server's XMLRPC API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:47
msgid ""
"``Failed``: list of responses for those peripheral servers the call failed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example Python Script for Relay Authentication:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "hubSessionKey = client.hub.loginWithAuthRelayMode(HUB_USERNAME, HUB_PASSWORD)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Authenticate those servers(same credentials will be used as of hub to authenticate)\n"
"client.hub.attachToServers(hubSessionKey, serverIds)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:55
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# Perform the needed operation\n"
"systemsPerServer = client.multicast.system.list_systems(hubSessionKey, serverIds)\n"
"successfulResponses = systemsPerServer[\"Successful\"][\"Responses\"]\n"
"failedResponses = systemsPerServer[\"Failed\"][\"Responses\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example: Auto-Connect Authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:59
msgid ""
"Auto-connect mode is similar to relay mode, it uses the Hub credentials to "
"sign in in to all peripheral servers.  However, there is no need to use the "
"``attachToServers`` method, as auto-connect mode connects to all available "
"peripheral servers.  This occurs at the same time as you sign in to the Hub."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:60
msgid "A typical workflow for auto-connect authentication is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:61
msgid ""
"Credentials for the Hub are passed to the ``loginWithAutoconnectMode`` "
"method, and a session key for the Hub is returned (``hubSessionKey``)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example Python Script for Auto-Connect Authentication:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-auth.adoc:72
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"loginResponse = client.hub.loginWithAutoconnectMode(HUB_USERNAME, HUB_PASSWORD)\n"
"hubSessionKey = loginResponse[\"SessionKey\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hub Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Before you begin, you need to install the ``hub-xmlrpc-api`` package, and "
"configure the Hub Server to use the API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Installing and Configuring the Hub XMLRPCÂ API"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:4
msgid ""
"On the HubÂ Server, or on a host that has access to all peripheral servers' "
"XMLRPC APIs, install the ``hub-xmlrpc-api`` package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:5
msgid ""
"The package is available in the {productname} {productnumber} repositories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:6
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Set the Hub XMLRPC API service to start automatically at boot "
"time, and start it immediately:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sudo systemctl enable hub-xmlrpc-api.service\n"
"sudo systemctl start hub-xmlrpc-api.service\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:8
msgid ""
"OPTIONAL: Check that these parameters in the [path]``/etc/hub/hub.conf`` "
"configuration file are correct:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:9
msgid "``HUB_API_URL``: URL to the Hub Server XMLRPC API endpoint."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Use the default value if you are installing `hub-xmlrpc-api` on the Hub "
"Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:11
msgid ""
"``HUB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT``: the maximum number of seconds to wait for a "
"response when connecting to a Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:12
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:14
msgid "Use the default value in most cases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:13
msgid ""
"``HUB_REQUEST_TIMEOUT``: the maximum number of seconds to wait for a "
"response when calling a Server method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:15
msgid ""
"``HUB_CONNECT_USING_SSL``: use HTTPS instead of HTTP for communicating with "
"peripheral Servers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:16
msgid "Recommended for a secure environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:17
msgid "Restart services to pick up configuration changes."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-install.adoc:18
msgid ""
"To use HTTPS to connect to peripheral Servers, you must set the "
"``HUB_CONNECT_USING_SSL`` parameter to ``true``, and ensure that the SSL "
"certificates for all the peripheral Servers are installed on the machine "
"where the ``hub-xmlrpc-api`` service runs.  Do this by copying the ``RHN-ORG-"
"TRUSTED-SSL-CERT`` certificate file from each peripheral Server's "
"[path]``http://<server-url>/pub/`` directory to [path]``/etc/pki/trust/"
"anchors/``, and run [command]``update-ca-certificates``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "HubÂ XMLRPC API Namespaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:2
msgid ""
"The Hub XMLRPC API operates in a similar way to the {productname} API.  For "
"{productname} API documentation, see https://documentation.suse.com/suma."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:3
msgid ""
"The Hub XMLRPC API exposes the same methods that are available from the "
"server's XMLRPC API, with a few differences in parameter and return types.  "
"Additionally, the Hub XMLRPC API supports some Hub-specific end points which "
"are not available in the {productname} API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:4
msgid "The Hub XMLRPC API supports three different namespaces:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:5
msgid "The ``hub`` namespace is used to target the Hub XMLRPC APIÂ Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:6
msgid ""
"It supports Hub-specific XMLRPC endpoints which are primarily related to "
"authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:7
msgid ""
"The ``unicast`` namespace is used to target a single server registered in "
"the hub."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:8
msgid ""
"It redirects any call transparently to one specific server and returns any "
"value as if the server's XMLRPC API endpoint was used directly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:9
msgid ""
"The ``multicast`` namespace is used to target multiple peripheral servers "
"registered in the hub."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:10
msgid ""
"It redirects any call transparently to all the specified servers and returns "
"the results in the form of a ``map``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:11
msgid ""
"If you do not specify a namespace, all calls are transparently redirected to "
"the underlying {productname} Server XMLRPC API of the Hub Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:12
msgid ""
"This allows you to call all available methods on the {productname} Server "
"XMLRPC API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Methods called without specifying any of the above namespaces will be "
"forwarded to the normal XMLRPC API of the hub.  This is the API exposed on "
"ports 80 and 443."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:14
msgid "Some important considerations for hub namespaces:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Individual server IDs can be obtained using ``client.hub."
"listServerIds(hubSessionKey)``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:16
msgid ""
"The ``unicast`` namespace assumes all methods receive ``hubSessionKey`` and "
"serverID as their first two parameters, then any other parameter as "
"specified by the regular Server API."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "client.unicast.[namespace].[methodName](hubSessionKey, serverId, param1, param2)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:18
msgid ""
"The ``hubSessionKey`` can be obtained using different authentication methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:19
msgid ""
"For more information, see xref:specialized-guides:large-deployments/hub-auth."
"adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:20
msgid ""
"The ``multicast`` namespace assumes all methods receive ``hubSessionKey``, a "
"list of ``ServerID`` values, then lists of per-server parameters as "
"specified by the regular server XMLRPC API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:21
msgid ""
"The return value is a ``map``, with ``Successful`` and ``Failed`` entries "
"for each server involved in the call."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-namespaces.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "client.multicast.[namespace].[methodname](hubSessionKey, [serverId1, serverId2], [param1_s1, param1_s2], [param2_s1, param2_s2])\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hub Reporting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:2
msgid ""
"The Hub prepares and provides content for multiple peripheral {productname} "
"Servers.  The goal of the reporting feature is to get data from these "
"Servers back and have combined reporting data available on the Hub.  The "
"data is made available for external Reporting Tools."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The main database is a PostgreSQL database in the {productname} Hub system.  "
"It stores all the information collected from all the servers, and aggregates "
"them.  Every peripheral Server has its own reporting database where the "
"information is collected for that system.  In summary:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:5
msgid ""
"the DB in {productname} Hub stores, collects and aggregates data coming from "
"all the DBs of the peripheral Servers,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:6
msgid ""
"the DB in {productname} Hub stores also its own data from the systems "
"directly connected and managed by the Hub,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:7
msgid "the DB in peripheral {productname} Server stores its own data,"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:8
msgid ""
"the reporting tool can be connected either to the Hub or to any "
"{productname} Server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The reporting database and schema are set up by default using the local "
"PostgreSQL server.  The reporting database is a separate database accessible "
"via the network."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:11
msgid ""
"As a requirement we expect all server certificates are signed by the same "
"Root Certificate Authority (CA).  The whole {productname} Hub environment "
"should be using only one Root CA."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create a DB user for the reporting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:13
msgid ""
"Before connecting an external Reporting Tools to the Database, a user with "
"read-only permission should be created.  For doing that, it is possible to "
"use ``uyuni-setup-reportdb-user``."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "usage: uyuni-setup-reportdb-user [options]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"options:\n"
"  --help\n"
"            show this help message and exit\n"
"  --non-interactive\n"
"            Switches to non-interactive mode\n"
"  --dbuser=DBUSER\n"
"            Report DB User\n"
"  --dbpassword=DBPASSWORD\n"
"            Report DB Password\n"
"  --add\n"
"            Add the new user\n"
"  --delete\n"
"            Delete the user\n"
"  --modify\n"
"            Set a new password\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Database Schema"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:17
msgid ""
"The schema exports the most important tables from the main {productname} "
"Database as a de-normalized variant containing only data which are relevant "
"for a report."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Ready-to-use reports are provided as views, aggregating data over multiple "
"tables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Every table gets an extra id column (`mgm_id`) specifying the {productname} "
"server which provided the data.  On a single {productname} Server this "
"column has the standard value `1` which represent [literal]``localhost``.  "
"On the {productname} Hub it is replaced with the real server id the managed "
"server has in the hub database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Another common additional field is `synced_date`, which represents the time "
"when the data were exported from the main {productname} Server database."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Schema documentation can be found on the Left Navigation Bar -> menu:"
"Help[Report Database Schema]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Data Generation and Update"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:23
msgid ""
"{productname} uses taskomatic jobs to generate the data for the reporting "
"database and to get the data from the peripheral servers to the hub."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:24
msgid ""
"To generate and update the data on a peripheral server, the responsible "
"schedule is called `update-reporting-default`.  It is executed by default "
"daily at midnight."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:25
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Hub there is a second schedule which is important.  To "
"fetch the reporting data from all registered peripheral servers, the task "
"with the name `update-reporting-hub-default` is executed daily at 1:30 AM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:26
msgid ""
"All times are in the local timezone of the server.  If the peripheral "
"servers are in different timezones, it is recommended to align all the "
"schedules.  Make sure that all reporting data are gathered at a specific "
"point in time, and `update-reporting-hub-default` is running when all "
"peripheral servers have actually finished their local jobs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tuning Reporting Jobs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "`report_db_batch_size`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Description          | The maximum number of rows fetched and written from one database to the other in one shot.\n"
"| Tune when            | Out of memory errors or on processing speed problems.\n"
"| Value default        | 2000\n"
"| Value recommendation | 500 - 5000\n"
"| Location             | [path]``/etc/rhn/rhn.conf``\n"
"| Example              | `report_db_batch_size = 4000`\n"
"| After changing       | Check xref:memory-usage[memory usage].\n"
"                         Monitor memory usage closely before and after the change.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "`report_db_hub_workers`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/large-deployments/hub-reporting.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
