#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:1
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/payg/aws/payg-aws-server-setup.adoc:1
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/payg/azure/payg-azure-server-setup.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initial setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:2
msgid ""
"This guide shows you the fastest way to get {productname} up and running in "
"a public cloud using on-demand or BYOS services.  We have tested using "
"{productname} on Amazon EC2, Google Compute Engine, and Microsoft Azure, but "
"these procedures should work with other public cloud providers as well, with "
"some variation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:3
msgid ""
"There are three main methods of using {productname} on a public cloud "
"service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "Bring your ownÂ subscription (BYOS)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:5
msgid ""
"Most public cloud providers make a BYOS image of {productname} available.  "
"This means you do not need to install {productname}, just set up the "
"server.  You will need to have {suse} product entitlements before you begin, "
"and there are some additional setup steps required.  The public cloud "
"documentation in the {productname} documentation suite assumes you are using "
"this method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid "Virtual machine on public cloud"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:7
msgid ""
"In this method, you subscribe to a public cloud service, and install "
"{productname} in a virtual machine, using the {unifiedinstaller}.  You will "
"need to have {suse} product entitlements before you begin.  You can do this "
"by following all the same instructions as you would for any local "
"{productname} installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "On-demand {sles} pay as you go (PAYG) image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Most public cloud providers make {sles} available as a BYOS image.  This "
"means that {sles} is pre-installed, and you can install {productname} on "
"top, using the {unifiedinstaller}.  You can do this by following all the "
"same instructions as you would for any local {productname} installation.  "
"You will need to have {suse} product entitlements before you begin.  Be "
"careful with this method, because you might end up requiring additional "
"product entitlements that could drive up your costs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:10
msgid ""
"If you are using the BYOS method, start by logging in to your chosen public "
"cloud provider, and launching a {productname} instance.  Depending on the "
"public cloud you are using, you can usually locate the {productname} Server "
"BYOS images by searching for ``suse manager``.  In EC2, you need to search "
"within the Community AMIs.  In GCE and Azure, search the marketplace."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Select a public cloud instance type that meets the hardware and networking "
"requirements in xref:installation-and-upgrade:pubcloud-requirements.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/byos/setup.adoc:12
msgid ""
"When you have your virtual machine ready, and the BYOS image installed, you "
"need to set up {productname}.  This is done in the same way as a local "
"installation, using {yast}.  When you have completed {productname} setup, "
"you need to activate the public cloud module.  You can then complete setup "
"in the {productname} {webui}.  For more information about setting up, see "
"xref:installation-and-upgrade:pubcloud-setup.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/overview.adoc:1
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/public-cloud-guide/payg-support.adoc:8
