#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:2
msgid ""
"{productname} uses formulas with forms to configure your SAP clients.  There "
"are two formulas that you need to use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:3
msgid "``Hana`` to configure the HANA database"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:4
msgid "``Cluster`` to configure the clients into a cluster"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:5
msgid ""
"The formulas are provided by packages that you can download with your "
"package manager.  You need to install the formulas on the {productname} "
"Server.  When you have installed the package, you can use the {productname} "
"{webui} to enable and configure the formulas.  As you go through the formula "
"configuration process, provide details of the clients that contain your SAP "
"cluster, to set them up appropriately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:6
msgid ""
"To install the formulas on the {productname} Server, use your package "
"manager to install these packages:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:7
msgid "``saphanabootstrap-formula``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:8
msgid "``sapnwbootstrap-formula``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:9
msgid "``drbd-formula``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:10
msgid "``habootstrap-formula``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:11
msgid "``salt-shaptools``"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:12
msgid ""
"The order that you enable and configure the formulas is important.  You must "
"enable, configure, and apply the HANA formula first.  Then you can enable, "
"configure, and apply the cluster formula.  If you perform these steps in the "
"wrong order, your SAP installation fails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable and Configure the HANAÂ Formula"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:14
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:23
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[System List] and "
"click the client to use as the primary client in the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Formulas`` tab, locate the ``Sap Hana "
"Deployment`` heading, and check the ``Saphanabootstrap`` formula in the "
"list.  Click btn:[Save] and apply the highstate to activate the formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:16
msgid ""
"When the formula is activated, navigate to the menu:Formulas[Hana] tab, and "
"complete the details in the form."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Make sure you check [guimenu]``Install required packages`` to install "
"everything you need on the client.  In the [guimenu]``Nodes`` sections, type "
"the short hostname of the client to install the HANA database or the "
"hostname you can retrieve on the command line with:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '<client-name>' grains.item host\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:19
msgid "Provide further details for the installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Complete the remaining details according to your environment, click btn:"
"[Save], and apply the highstate.  When the highstate is complete, you can go "
"on to apply the cluster formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "suma_sap_hana_formula.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enable and Configure the Cluster Formula"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:24
msgid ""
"Navigate to the [guimenu]``Formulas`` tab, locate the ``Cluster`` heading, "
"and check the ``Habootstrap`` formula in the list.  Click btn:[Save] and "
"apply the highstate to activate the formula."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "suma_sap_formulas.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:26
msgid ""
"When the formula is activated, navigate to the menu:Formulas[Cluster] tab, "
"and complete the details in the form."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:27
msgid ""
"Make sure you check [guimenu]``Install required packages`` to install "
"everything you need on the client.  Give your cluster a name, and specify "
"the hostname of the primary client in the cluster."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:28
msgid ""
"Complete the remaining details according to your environment, click btn:"
"[Save], and apply the highstate."
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/configure.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "suma_sap_cluster_formula.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/overview.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Quick Start: SAP Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/overview.adoc:3
msgid ""
"This guide shows you how to use {productname} to install and configure "
"anÂ SAP cluster.  It guides you through setting up a single {productname} "
"Server, preparing your client systems, and configuring the cluster using "
"formulas."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/overview.adoc:4
msgid ""
"For more information about SAP, see the SAP documentation at https://"
"documentation.suse.com/sles-sap."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/overview.adoc:5
msgid ""
"For more information about {productname}, see the {productname} "
"documentation at https://documentation.suse.com/suma."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing Clients"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Your SAP cluster requires several client systems.  Prepare your clients on "
"physical or virtual hardware, and ensure you have {sles}{nbsp}15 for SAP "
"installation media ready.  You cannot create an SAP cluster without the "
"{sles} SAP extension, as it provides tooling specific to SAP."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:3
msgid ""
"One of the key features of SAP is high availability of the cluster.  Every "
"component within an SAP cluster has redundancy and failover protection.  "
"When you are preparing your clients, ensure you have enough hardware and "
"infrastructure to allow for this.  For more information about hardware "
"requirements, see https://documentation.suse.com/sles-sap/15-SP4/html/SLES-"
"SAP-installation/cha-plan.html#sec-hardware"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:4
msgid ""
"For more information about the clients you need to set up for an SAP "
"cluster, see https://documentation.suse.com/sbp/all[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid "Register Clients to the {SCC}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Each client within your SAP cluster must be registered with the {scc}.  To "
"obtain your registration code, navigate to https://scc.suse.com/login in "
"your web browser.  Log in to your SCC account, or follow the prompts to "
"create a new account.  Click the btn:[Subscriptions] tab to see the "
"registration code.  When you install {sles}{nbsp}15 for SAP the "
"{unifiedinstaller} prompts you for the code."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:7
msgid ""
"For more information about registering {productname} with {scc}, see xref:"
"installation-and-upgrade:general-requirements.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure the Clients for Clustering"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Every client system must have all the other client systems listed in their "
"[path]``/etc/hosts`` file.  Open the [path]``/etc/hosts`` file on each "
"client, and add the hostname for each of the other clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create a Shared Storage Device"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:11
msgid ""
"Each of the clients needs to be able to access a shared disk.  The shared "
"disk can be physical hardware connected by ethernet, or you can set up a "
"virtual disk and access it with iSCSI."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:12
msgid ""
"If you use a virtual disk, consider hosting it on a separate system.  Do not "
"use a client machine to host the shared storage disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download the SAP Installation Software"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Download the SAP installation media and save a copy on each client.  The "
"software that you require differs depending on your environment.  For "
"example, if you are using HANA, you need the SAP HANA platform.  If you are "
"using Netweaver, you need different packages.  These software packages are "
"provided by SAP, not by {suse}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Ensure you have saved the installation software in the same file system "
"location on each client.  Alternatively, save it to a shared NFS drive."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configure Clients to Use Latest ``module.run``"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Each client needs to be configured to use the latest version of ``module."
"run``.  On each of the client machines, open the ``/etc/salt/minion`` "
"configuration file and add or edit this line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"use_superseded:\n"
"  - module.run\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:19
msgid "Restart the ``salt-minion`` process to enable the changes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "systemctl restart salt-minion\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install Additional Disks for HANA"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:22
msgid ""
"For the clients that are going to run the HANA database, you require an "
"additional storage device.  This device is used to store files required by "
"HANA, which are located in the [path]``/hana/`` directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:23
msgid ""
"We recommend that this storage device be at least 20{nbsp}GB.  For some "
"installations, you might require more, and it is possible to use multiple "
"disks to provide this storage.  For comprehensive hardware requirements, see "
"https://documentation.suse.com/sbp/all[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "Register Clients to the Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:25
msgid ""
"First of all, make sure you have an activation key that is associated with "
"the ``SLE-Product-SLES_SAP15`` base channel.  For more information about "
"activation keys, see xref:client-configuration:activation-keys.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:26
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[Bootstrapping].  Fill "
"in the appropriate details, and make sure you check the [guimenu]``Manage "
"System Completely via SSH`` checkbox.  In the [guimenu]``Activation Key`` "
"field, select the SLES for SAP activation key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-clients.adoc:27
msgid ""
"For more information about registering, see xref:client-configuration:"
"registration-webui.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prepare Server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Before you start you need to install the {productname} Server.  The method "
"for installing the {productname} Server varies depending on your hardware "
"and environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:3
msgid ""
"{productname} is installed using the {sles}{nbsp}15 {unifiedinstaller}.  "
"During the installation process, when you are prompted for which product to "
"install, select {productname} Server.  The server does not need to have the "
"{sles}{nbsp}15 with SAP product installed.  For more information about "
"installing the {productname} Server, see xref:installation-and-upgrade:"
"install-server-unified.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:4
msgid ""
"When the {productname} Server is installed, set it up by running the "
"[command]``yast2 susemanager_setup`` command from the command prompt.  The "
"setup script prompts you to complete additional details about your server, "
"and give you the URL to use to access the {webui}.  For more information "
"about setup, see xref:installation-and-upgrade:server-setup.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:5
msgid ""
"You need to do some configuration to set up the {productname} {webui}.  In "
"your browser, navigate to the URL of the server, and configure your "
"administration access to the {webui}.  For more information about setting up "
"the {webui}, see xref:installation-and-upgrade:webui-setup.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:6
msgid ""
"Now you can use the {webui} to prepare software channels and activation keys "
"for your clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:7
msgid ""
"On the {productname} Server, add the appropriate SAP channels: From the "
"{webui}, add [systemitem]``SUSEÂ Linux Enterprise Server 15 for SAP``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Synchronize the {productname} Server with the {SCC}.  You can do this using "
"the {webui}.  Add the new channel to your activation key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:9
msgid ""
"To check if a channel has finished synchronizing navigate to menu:"
"Admin[Setup Wizard] and select the [guimenu]``Products`` tab.  This dialog "
"displays a completion bar for each product when they are being synchronized."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:10
msgid ""
"Software channels can be very large.  The initial channel synchronization "
"can sometimes take up to several hours."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/qs-sap/prepare-server.adoc:11
msgid ""
"When the initial synchronization is complete, we recommended you clone the "
"channel before you work with it.  This gives you a backup of the original "
"synchronization data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:2
msgid ""
"Salt commands have three main components: target, function, and arguments.  "
"The calls are constructed in this format:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt 'target' <function> [arguments]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The target defines the client, or group of clients, on which to run the "
"function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:5
msgid "The function is the particular task to be run."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:6
msgid "Arguments provide any extra data required by the function."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Targets"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:8
msgid ""
"Salt command targets allow you to specify a client or group of clients.  "
"There are several different targets you can use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "General Targeting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:10
msgid "List available grains on all clients:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:11
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-useful-commands.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' grains.ls\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:12
msgid "Target a specific client:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt 'web1.example.com' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "Glob Targeting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:15
msgid "Target all clients using a particular domain:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*example.com' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:17
msgid "Target all clients using a particular label:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt 'label*' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "List Targeting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:20
msgid "Specify a flat list of clients, using their IDs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt -L 'client_ID1, client_ID2, client_ID3' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Regular Expression Targeting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:23
msgid "You can also define targets with PCRE-compliant regular expressions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt -E '(?!web)' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "IP Address Targeting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:26
msgid "List available client IP addresses:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' network.ip_addrs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:28
msgid "Target a specific client IP address:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt -S '172.31.60.74' test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:30
msgid "Target all clients on a subnet:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt -S 172.31.0.0/16 test.ping\n"
msgstr ""

#
#. This is general Linux info, not specific to the topic.
#. You can use the [command]``ip`` command to find the subnet mask in the format of ``192.168.1.1/24``:
#. ----
#. ip -o -f inet addr show | awk '/scope global/ {print $4}'
#. ----
#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:32
msgid ""
"For more on targeting, see https://docs.saltstack.com/en/latest/topics/"
"targeting/."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Execution Modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:34
msgid ""
"When you have specified a target, provide the module and function to execute "
"on the target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:35
msgid "Find which modules can be executed on the target:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' sys.doc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:37
msgid ""
"For a full list of callable modules, see https://docs.saltstack.com/en/"
"latest/ref/modules/all/index.html."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "Salt Function Arguments"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:39
msgid "Functions accept arguments for any extra data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:40
msgid ""
"For example, the [command]``pkg.install`` function requires an argument "
"specifying which package to install:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' pkg.install yast2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:42
msgid ""
"You can provide more than one argument to a function, with spaces between "
"them.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-command.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "salt '*' cmd.run 'echo \"Hello: $FIRST_NAME\"' env='{FIRST_NAME: \"John\"}'\n"
