#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "Custom State to Trust a GPGÂ Key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:46
msgid ""
"By default, operating systems trust only their own GPG keys when they are "
"installed, and do not trust keys provided by third party packages.  The "
"clients can be successfully bootstrapped without the GPG key being trusted.  "
"However, you cannot install new third party packages or update them until "
"the keys are trusted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:47
msgid ""
"Salt clients are set to trust {suse} tools channels GPG keys when they are "
"bootstrapped.  For all other clients and channels, you need to manually "
"trust third party GPG keys."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:48
msgid ""
"If you are bootstrapping Salt clients from the {productname} {webui}, you "
"can use a custom Salt state to trust the GPGÂ key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "Procedure: Trusting a GPGÂ Key With a Custom Salt State"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:50
msgid ""
"Locate the key that you need to trust.  Ensure you have the correct key, and "
"that you also have the fingerprint used to verify the key.  This information "
"is available from the vendor or, in some cases, from a key server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:51
msgid ""
"Copy the key to a file location where the client can access it.  We "
"recommend saving it in the [path]``/srv/www/htdocs/pub/`` directory, where "
"all {suse} public keys are also saved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:54
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Name`` field, type a name for your state.  For example, "
"``GPGÂ Key Trusts``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:55
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Label`` field, type a label.  For example, "
"``GPG_Key_Trusts``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:56
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``Description`` field, type a short description of the "
"configuration your state performs.  For example, ``Trusts GPGÂ Keys for "
"CentOS``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:57
msgid ""
"In the [guimenu]``SLSÂ Contents`` field, create a state to retrieve the "
"appropriate key from the {productname} Server and trust it on the client.  "
"The exact contents of your state varies depending on your client operating "
"system.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:58
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rpm_trust_gpg_key:\n"
"  cmd.run:\n"
"    - name: rpm --import https://{{ salt['pillar.get']('mgr_server') }}/pub/<third-party-gpg>.key\n"
"    - unless: rpm -q gpg-pubkey-<key_id>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"deb_trust_gpg_key:\n"
"  mgrcompat.module_run:\n"
"    - name: pkg.add_repo_key\n"
"    - path: https://{{ salt['pillar.get']('mgr_server') }}/pub/<third-party-gpg>.key\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  Alternatively, you can add GPG keys to a configuration channel, using a managed file to deploy them directly on the client.\n"
"  In this case, you would use a local path to the key, rather than a URL.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigate to menu:Configuration[Channels] and click the name of the state you want to assign a client to.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigate to the menu:Systems[Target Systems] tab and check the clients you want to assign.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "Click btn:[Subscribe systems].\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "When the configuration file is next run on the client, the GPG key is trusted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-custom-states.adoc:66
