msgid "Custom Salt Formulas"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:2
msgid ""
"You can also write your own custom formulas, and make them available to your "
"clients in the {productname} {webui}.  This section contains information "
"about writing custom formulas, including formulas with forms."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:3
msgid ""
"For information about the formulas provided by {productname}, see xref:"
"specialized-guides:salt/salt-formulas-by-product.adoc[]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid "File Structure Overview"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:5
msgid ""
"RPM-based formulas must be placed in a specific directory structure to "
"ensure that they work correctly.  A formula contains two separate "
"directories: [path]``states``, and [path]``metadata``.  Folders in these "
"directories need to have exactly matching names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:6
msgid ""
"The formula states directory contains anything necessary for a Salt state to "
"work independently.  This includes [path]``.sls`` files, a [path]``map."
"jinja`` file and any other required files.  This directory should only be "
"modified by RPMs and should not be edited manually.  For example, the "
"[package]``locale-formula`` states directory is located in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "/usr/share/susemanager/formulas/states/locale/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:8
msgid ""
"To create formulas with forms, the metadata directory contains a "
"[path]``form.yml`` file.  The [path]``form.yml`` file defines the forms for "
"{productname}.  The metadata directoy also contains an optional "
"[path]``metadata.yml`` file that contains additional information about a "
"formula.  For example, the [package]``locale-formula`` metadata directory is "
"located in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "/usr/share/susemanager/formulas/metadata/locale/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:10
msgid ""
"If you have a custom formula that is not in an RPM, it must be in a state "
"directory configured as a Salt file root.  Custom state formula data must be "
"in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "/srv/salt/<custom-formula-name>/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:12
msgid "Custom metadata information must be in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "/srv/formula_metadata/<custom-formula-name>/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:14
msgid ""
"All custom folders must contain a [path]``form.yml`` file.  These files are "
"detected as form recipes and are applied to groups and systems from the "
"{webui}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "/srv/formula_metadata/<custom-formula-name>/form.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:16
msgid ""
"The Salt formula directory changed in {productname}{nbsp}4.0.  The old "
"directory location, [path]``/usr/share/susemanager/formulas``, will continue "
"to work for some time.  You should ensure that you update to the new "
"directory location, [path]``/usr/share/salt-formulas/`` as soon as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Define Formula with Forms Data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:18
msgid ""
"{productname} requires a file called [path]``form.yml``, to describe how "
"formula data should look within the {webui}.  The [path]``form.yml`` file is "
"used by {productname} to generate the desired formula with forms, with "
"values editable by a user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:19
msgid ""
"The file contains a list of editable attributes that start with a `$` sign.  "
"These attributes are used to determine how to display the formula in the "
"{productname} {webui}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:20
msgid ""
"For example, the [path]``form.yml`` that is included with the "
"[package]``locale-formula`` is in:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "/usr/share/susemanager/formulas/metadata/locale/form.yml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:22
msgid "Part of that file looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"timezone:\n"
"  $type: group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  name:\n"
"    $type: select\n"
"    $values: [\"CET\",\n"
"              \"Etc/Zulu\"\n"
"              ]\n"
"    $default: CET\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  hardware_clock_set_to_utc:\n"
"    $type: boolean\n"
"    $default: True\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:26
msgid ""
"All values that start with a `$` sign are annotations used to display the UI "
"that users interact with.  These annotations are not part of pillar data "
"itself and are handled as metadata."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:27
msgid "This section lists the available attributes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "$type"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:29
msgid ""
"The most important attribute is the `$type` attribute.  It defines the type "
"of the pillar value and the form-field that is generated.  The supported "
"types are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:30
msgid "`text`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:31
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-ssh.adoc:83
msgid "`password`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:32
msgid "`number`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:33
msgid "`url`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:34
msgid "`email`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:35
msgid "`date`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:36
msgid "`time`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:37
msgid "`datetime`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:38
msgid "`boolean`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:39
msgid "`color`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:40
msgid "`select`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:41
msgid "`group`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:42
msgid "`edit-group`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:43
msgid "`namespace`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:44
msgid "`hidden-group` (obsolete, renamed to ``namespace``)"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:45
msgid ""
"The text attribute is the default and does not need to be specified "
"explicitly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:46
msgid "Many of these values are self-explanatory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:47
msgid "The `text` type generates a simple text field"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:48
msgid "The `password` type generates a password field"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:49
msgid "The `color` type generates a color picker"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:50
msgid ""
"The ``group``, ``edit-group``, and `namespace` (formerly ``hidden-group``) "
"types do not generate an editable field and are used to structure form and "
"pillar data.  All these types support nesting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:51
msgid ""
"The `group` and `namespace` types differ slightly.  The `group` type "
"generates a visible border with a heading.  The `namespace` type shows "
"nothing visually, and is only used to structure pillar data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:52
msgid ""
"The `edit-group` type allows you to structure and restrict editable fields "
"in a more flexible way.  The `edit-group` type is a collection of items of "
"the same kind.  Collections can have these four shapes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:53
msgid "List of primitive items"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:54
msgid "List of dictionaries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:55
msgid "Dictionary of primitive items"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:56
msgid "Dictionary of dictionaries"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:57
msgid ""
"The size of each collection is variable.  Users can add or remove elements."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:58
msgid ""
"For example, `edit-group` supports the `$minItems` and `$maxItems` "
"attributes, which simplifies complex and repeatable input structures.  "
"These, and also `itemName`, are optional."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "$default"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:60
msgid ""
"Allows you to specify a default value to be displayed.  This default value "
"will be used if no other value is entered.  In an `edit-group` it allows you "
"to create initial members of the group and populate them with specified data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "$optional"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:62
msgid ""
"This type is a Boolean attribute.  If it is `true` and the field is empty in "
"the form, then this field will not be generated in the formula data and the "
"generated dictionary will not contain the field name key.  If it is `false` "
"and the field is empty, the formula data will contain a `<field name>: null` "
"entry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:63
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ifEmpty"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:64
msgid ""
"This type is used if the field is empty.  This usually occurs because the "
"user did not provide a value.  The `ifEmpty` type can only be used when "
"`$optional` is `false` or not defined.  If `$optional` is `true`, then "
"`$ifEmpty` is ignored.  In this example, the `DP2` string would be used if "
"the user leaves the field empty:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"displayName:\n"
"  $type: string\n"
"  $ifEmpty: DP2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "$name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:67
msgid ""
"Allows you to specify the name of a value that is shown in the form.  If "
"this value is not set, the pillar name is used and capitalized without "
"underscores and dashes.  Reference it in the same section with ``pass:"
"c[${name}]``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "$help and $placeholder"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:69
msgid ""
"These attributes are used to give a user a better understanding of what the "
"value should be.  The `$help` type defines the message a user sees when "
"hovering over a field The `$placeholder` type displays a gray placeholder "
"text in the field"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:70
msgid ""
"Use `$placeholder` only with text fields like text, password, email or date "
"fields.  Do not add a placeholder if you also use `$default`, as it will "
"hide the placeholder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "$key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:72
msgid ""
"Applicable only if the `edit-group` has the shape of a dictionary.  When the "
"pillar data is a dictionary, the `$key` attribute determines the key of an "
"entry in the dictionary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:73
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-states-and-pillars.adoc:5
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-states-and-pillars.adoc:53
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"user_passwords:\n"
"  $type: edit-group\n"
"  $minItems: 1\n"
"  $prototype:\n"
"    $key:\n"
"        $type: text\n"
"    $type: text\n"
"  $default:\n"
"    alice: secret-password\n"
"    bob: you-shall-not-pass\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:75
msgid "Pillar:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"user_passwords:\n"
"  alice:\n"
"    secret-password\n"
"  bob:\n"
"    you-shall-not-pass\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "$minItems and $maxItems"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:78
msgid ""
"In an ``edit-group``, `$minItems` and `$maxItems` specifies the lowest and "
"highest numbers for the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "$itemName"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:80
msgid ""
"In an ``edit-group``, `$itemName` defines a template for the name to be used "
"for the members of the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "$prototype"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:82
msgid ""
"In an ``edit-group``, `$prototype` is mandatory and defines the default pre-"
"filled values for newly added members in the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "$scope"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:84
msgid ""
"Specifies a hierarchy level at which a value may be edited.  Possible values "
"are ``system``, `group`, and ``readonly``."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:85
msgid ""
"The default value is `$scope: system`, allows values to be edited at group "
"and system levels.  A value can be entered for each system but if no value "
"is entered the system will fall back to the group default."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:86
msgid ""
"The ``$scope: group`` option makes a value editable only for a group.  On "
"the system level you will be able to see the value, but not edit it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:87
msgid ""
"The `$scope: readonly` option makes a field read-only.  It can be used to "
"show data to the user, but will not allow them to edit it.  This option "
"should be used in combination with the ``$default`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "$visibleIf"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:89
msgid "Deprecated in favor of `$visible`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:90
msgid ""
"Allows you to show a field or group if a simple condition is met.  An "
"example condition is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "some_group#another_group#my_checkbox == true\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:92
msgid ""
"The left part of the condition is the path to another value, and groups are "
"separated by `#` signs.  The middle section of the condition should be "
"either `==` for a value to be equal or `!=` for values that should be not "
"equal.  The last field in the statement can be any value which a field "
"should have or not have."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:93
msgid ""
"The field with this attribute associated with it will be shown only when the "
"condition is met.  In this example the field will be shown only if "
"`my_checkbox` is checked.  The ability to use conditional statements is not "
"limited to check boxes.  It may also be used to check values of select-"
"fields, text-fields, and similar."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:94
msgid "A check box should be structured like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:95
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:99
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:117
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:140
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"some_group:\n"
"  $type: group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:96
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:100
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:118
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:141
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:150
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  another_group:\n"
"    $type: group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:97
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:119
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:142
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"      my_checkbox:\n"
"        $type: boolean\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:98
msgid ""
"Relative paths can be specified using prefix dots.  One dot indicates a "
"sibling, two dots indicate a parent, and so on.  This is mostly useful for "
"``edit-group``."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:101
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:151
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    my_checkbox:\n"
"      $type: boolean\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    my_text:\n"
"      $visibleIf: .my_checkbox == true\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:103
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  yet_another_group:\n"
"    $type: group\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    my_text2:\n"
"      $visibleIf: ..another_group#my_checkbox == true\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:105
msgid ""
"If you use multiple groups with the attribute, you can allow a users to "
"select an option and show a completely different form, dependent upon the "
"selected value."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:106
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:124
msgid ""
"Values from hidden fields can be merged into the pillar data and sent to the "
"client.  A formula must check the condition again and use the appropriate "
"data.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: modules/specialized-guides/pages/salt/salt-formulas-custom.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show_option:\n"
"  $type: checkbox\n"
"some_text:\n"
